Herewith a list of the winners of the  Golden Palm for the last 20 years:
1974: "The Conversation" by Francis Ford Coppola, US.
1975: "Chronicle of the Burning Years" by Mohammed Lakhdar-Hamina, Algeria.
1976: "Taxi Driver" by Martin Scorsese, US.
1977: "Padre Padrone" by Paolo and Vittorio Taviani, Italy.
1978: "The Tree of Wooden Clogs" by Ermanno Olmi, Italy.
1979: "Apocalypse Now" by Francis Ford Coppola, US.
"The Tin Drum" by Volker Schloendorff, Germany.
1980: "Kagemusha," by Akira Kurosawa, Japan.
"All That Jazz" by Bob Fosse, US.
1981: "Man of Iron, by Andrzej Wajda, Poland.
1982: "Missing" by Costa Gavras, US.
"Yol" by Yilmaz Guney, Turkey.
1983: "The Ballad of Narayama," by Shohei Imamura, Japan.
1984: "Paris Texas" by Wim Wenders, Germany.
1985: "When Father was away on Business" by Emir Kusturica, Yugoslavia.
1986: "Mission" by Roland Joffe, Britain.
1987: "Under Satan's Sun" by Maurice Pialat, France.
1988: "Pelle the Conqueror" by Bille August, Denmark.
1989: "Sex, Lies and Videotape" by Steven Sonderbergh, US.
1990: "Wild at Heart" by David Lynch, US.
1991: "Barton Fink" by Joel and Ethan Coen, US.
1992: "The Best Intentions" by Bille August, Denmark
1993: "The Piano" by Jane Campion, Australia
"Farewell to My Concubine" by Chen Kaige, China.
